21// This reducer is part of the JavaScript pipeline and contains lowering of
22// wasm nodes (from inlined wasm functions).
23//
24// The reducer replaces all TrapIf nodes with a conditional goto to deferred
25// code containing a call to the trap builtin.
26template <class Next>
27class WasmJSLoweringReducer : public Next {
28 public:
29 TURBOSHAFT_REDUCER_BOILERPLATE(WasmJSLowering)
30
31 V<None> REDUCE(TrapIf)(V<Word32> condition, OptionalV<FrameState> frame_state,
32 bool negated, TrapId trap_id) {
33 // All TrapIf nodes in JS need to have a FrameState.
34 DCHECK(frame_state.valid());
35 Builtin trap = static_cast<Builtin>(trap_id);
36 // The call is not marked as Operator::kNoDeopt. While it cannot actually
37 // deopt, deopt info based on the provided FrameState is required for stack
38 // trace creation of the wasm trap.
39 const bool needs_frame_state = true;
40 const CallDescriptor* tf_descriptor = GetBuiltinCallDescriptor(
41 trap, Asm().graph_zone(), StubCallMode::kCallBuiltinPointer,
42 needs_frame_state, Operator::kNoProperties);
43 const TSCallDescriptor* ts_descriptor = TSCallDescriptor::Create(
44 tf_descriptor, CanThrow::kYes, Asm().graph_zone());
45
46 V<FrameState> new_frame_state =
47 CreateFrameStateWithUpdatedBailoutId(frame_state.value());
48 V<Word32> should_trap = negated ? __ Word32Equal(condition, 0) : condition;
49 IF (UNLIKELY(should_trap)) {
50 OpIndex call_target = __ NumberConstant(static_cast<int>(trap));
51 __ Call(call_target, new_frame_state, {}, ts_descriptor);
52 __ Unreachable(); // The trap builtin never returns.
53 }
54
55 return V<None>::Invalid();
56 }
57
58 private:
59 OpIndex CreateFrameStateWithUpdatedBailoutId(OpIndex frame_state) {
60 // Create new FrameState with the correct source position (the position of
61 // the trap location).
62 const FrameStateOp& frame_state_op =
63 Asm().output_graph().Get(frame_state).template Cast<FrameStateOp>();
64 const FrameStateData* data = frame_state_op.data;
65 const FrameStateInfo& info = data->frame_state_info;
66
67 OpIndex origin = Asm().current_operation_origin();
68 DCHECK(origin.valid());
69 int offset = __ input_graph().source_positions()[origin].ScriptOffset();
70
71 const FrameStateInfo* new_info =
72 Asm().graph_zone()->template New<FrameStateInfo>(
73 BytecodeOffset(offset), info.state_combine(), info.function_info());
74 FrameStateData* new_data = Asm().graph_zone()->template New<FrameStateData>(
75 FrameStateData{*new_info, data->instructions, data->machine_types,
76 data->int_operands});
77 return __ FrameState(frame_state_op.inputs(), frame_state_op.inlined,
78 new_data);
79 }
80
81 Isolate* isolate_ = __ data() -> isolate();
82 SourcePositionTable* source_positions_ = __ data() -> source_positions();
83};
